WEBVTT

00:01.751 --> 00:03.962
<i>♪ In all this crazy world ♪</i>

00:03.962 --> 00:07.757
<i>♪ There's one thing I am certain of ♪</i>

00:07.757 --> 00:13.763
<i>♪ For every hour and month
and year that we are here to love ♪</i>

00:13.763 --> 00:16.766
<i>♪ Regardless of how much ♪</i>

00:16.766 --> 00:19.811
<i>♪ We talk, we tell, we touch ♪</i>

00:19.811 --> 00:25.608
<i>♪ No matter what we suffer throoough ♪</i>

00:25.608 --> 00:28.528
<i>♪ I can never know you ♪</i>

00:28.528 --> 00:32.198
<i>♪ I can never know you ♪</i>

00:32.198 --> 00:37.579
<i>♪ Can I ever know you ♪</i>

00:43.877 --> 00:45.336
My fellow members

00:45.336 --> 00:48.715
of The Sixth Street Community
Center's Writing Workshop:

00:48.715 --> 00:51.801
Beginners through
Intermediates,

00:51.801 --> 00:53.928
you hold in your hands today

00:53.928 --> 00:58.475
more... than just
the first chapter of my novel.

00:58.475 --> 01:01.978
You also hold... my heart.

01:02.896 --> 01:05.523
Am I nervous? A little.

01:05.523 --> 01:08.401
Am I nauseous? (chuckles) Extremely.

01:08.401 --> 01:10.904
But mostly, I am excited

01:10.904 --> 01:14.574
because I know that your mixed,

01:14.574 --> 01:18.828
but largely positive feedback
is going to serve

01:18.828 --> 01:24.417
as the gentle nudge
that I need to tell myself

01:24.417 --> 01:27.587
- that I am a writer!

01:27.587 --> 01:28.797
I have something to say

01:28.797 --> 01:31.091
and the world is a better place with me--

01:31.091 --> 01:32.967
- Touch of a man.
- Okay, no.

01:34.135 --> 01:35.720
I am not letting you do this.

01:35.720 --> 01:36.805
This is my day.

01:36.805 --> 01:38.515
I just don't get it, Linds.

01:38.515 --> 01:41.309
If you know for a fact
that you're a terrible writer...

01:41.309 --> 01:42.852
I'm not a terrible writer.

01:42.852 --> 01:45.396
...then why would you agree
to share that terrible writing

01:45.396 --> 01:47.607
beyond the confines of your own sad self?

01:47.607 --> 01:51.194
Everything is telling you
the same thing, sweetheart:

01:51.194 --> 01:54.614
you made a mistake. Leaving Ned?

01:54.614 --> 01:55.990
Nothing is telling me that.

01:55.990 --> 01:57.408
You, you were almost decapitated

01:57.408 --> 01:59.369
by a falling air conditioner
two weeks ago.

01:59.369 --> 02:02.122
- That was a sign.
- I survived, didn't I?

02:02.122 --> 02:06.209
- You've been hit by three cabs.
- At very low speeds.

02:06.209 --> 02:07.627
It's time to give up

02:07.627 --> 02:11.047
whatever this prolonged
emotional breakdown is

02:11.047 --> 02:12.799
and come home.

02:13.716 --> 02:17.637
I belong here...
In this city. In this vocation.

02:17.637 --> 02:18.930
And today is gonna prove it.

02:19.389 --> 02:21.683
Everybody is gonna love my chapter.

02:21.683 --> 02:23.476
You have no reason to believe that.

02:23.476 --> 02:24.477
Is that so?

02:24.727 --> 02:26.729
How about, uh,

02:26.729 --> 02:28.398
this reason?

02:28.940 --> 02:31.067
Well, you never count the first card.

02:31.067 --> 02:34.612
Everybody knows that.
What about this reason?

02:35.613 --> 02:38.074
It's funny. The devil's actually
a very misunderstood card

02:38.074 --> 02:40.160
because it's really more
about the shadow--

02:40.160 --> 02:43.872
<i>♪ When you're wondering
how something's gonna go ♪</i>

02:43.872 --> 02:47.292
<i>♪ Something there's
no way for you to know ♪</i>

02:47.292 --> 02:53.298
<i>♪ Just go and ask the universe
to show a spark of the divine ♪</i>

02:53.298 --> 02:56.176
<i>♪ I know, I say, "Hello! It's me!"♪</i>

02:56.176 --> 02:57.886
<i>♪ And insert deity ♪</i>

02:57.886 --> 03:01.181
<i>♪ Will always send a sign ♪</i>

03:01.181 --> 03:04.601
<i>♪ Like right now ♪</i>

03:04.601 --> 03:08.188
<i>♪ The sun is shinin', the sky is blue ♪</i>

03:08.188 --> 03:11.482
<i>♪ You'd only know
from your roommate's view ♪</i>

03:11.482 --> 03:15.278
<i>- ♪ And the kitchen's clean ♪
- ♪ But the bathroom's not ♪</i>

03:15.278 --> 03:17.030
<i>♪ She used your Nair and left
the hair ♪</i>

03:17.363 --> 03:18.531
<i>♪ and it smells like
poop and pot ♪</i>

03:18.740 --> 03:21.951
<i>♪ But they lowered rent
for the entire A and C line ♪</i>

03:21.951 --> 03:25.496
<i>♪ It's a sign, it's a sign ♪</i>

03:25.496 --> 03:29.209
JOAN/TOM/CELESTE:
<i>♪ It's a sign, it's a sign ♪</i>

03:29.209 --> 03:30.919
<i>♪ That's a sign all right ♪</i>

03:30.919 --> 03:32.670
JOAN/TOM/CELESTE: <i>♪ In black and white ♪</i>

03:32.670 --> 03:35.173
And you tell yourself, "Oh,
it's only a little rat bite."

03:35.173 --> 03:37.133
Ten days later, your spleen has swollen

03:37.133 --> 03:39.052
- to the size of a ripe melon.

03:39.052 --> 03:42.639
<i>- ♪ Note the broken mirror ♪
- ♪ And the haunted doll ♪</i>

03:42.639 --> 03:46.142
<i>♪ But encouraging graffiti
on the lovely wall ♪</i>

03:46.142 --> 03:48.019
<i>♪ Look, a big black cat ♪</i>

03:48.019 --> 03:49.771
<i>♪ I just won't go that way ♪</i>

03:49.771 --> 03:53.483
<i>♪ Hot damn, it looks like BAM
is doing the Scottish play ♪</i>

03:53.691 --> 03:56.611
<i>♪ But someone dropped their subway token
and now it's mine ♪</i>

03:56.611 --> 04:00.198
JOAN/TOM/CELESTE:
<i>♪ It's a sign, it's a sign ♪</i>

04:00.198 --> 04:03.910
<i>♪ It's a sign, it's a sign ♪</i>

04:03.910 --> 04:07.330
<i>- ♪ Is this glue or gum ♪
- ♪ No, that is cum ♪</i>

04:07.330 --> 04:10.041
Mm, dehydrated ejaculate.

04:10.041 --> 04:13.795
<i>♪ Today I really need things to go right ♪</i>

04:13.795 --> 04:17.298
<i>♪ 'Cause then I'll feel
that my future is bright ♪</i>

04:17.298 --> 04:19.842
<i>♪ And I'll know writing is right ♪</i>

04:19.842 --> 04:22.512
<i>♪ And I can write my ticket out of hell ♪</i>

04:22.512 --> 04:25.682
<i>♪ Oh, hell-o, mind if I squeeze in ♪</i>

04:25.682 --> 04:27.892
<i>♪ Look I just got a seat ♪</i>

04:27.892 --> 04:31.271
<i>♪ This baby's suckin' at New York's teat ♪</i>

04:31.271 --> 04:35.900
<i>♪ Sweet, or it's a sign you'll
end up like this fine man ♪</i>

04:35.900 --> 04:40.863
<i>♪ Drinkin' wine and slurpin'
tuna right out of a caaan ♪</i>

04:40.863 --> 04:44.784
<i>♪ Whoo, right on time
with seconds to spare ♪</i>

04:44.784 --> 04:48.705
<i>♪ Note the splatter of blood
at the base of the stairs ♪</i>

04:48.871 --> 04:52.250
<i>- ♪ There's seven writers ♪
- ♪ In room thirteen ♪</i>

04:52.250 --> 04:54.168
<i>♪ I got a hunch I wowed the bunch ♪</i>

04:54.168 --> 04:55.878
<i>♪ 'Cause your work is obscene ♪</i>

04:55.878 --> 04:57.547
Lindsay Arthur?

04:57.714 --> 04:59.382
<i>♪ And hey, they chose to start with me ♪</i>

04:59.382 --> 05:01.092
<i>♪ It's my turn to shine ♪</i>

05:01.384 --> 05:03.803
I need to speak to you. In private.

05:04.345 --> 05:06.431
You won't be coming back.

05:06.639 --> 05:08.391
<i>- ♪ Check and mate ♪
- ♪ Resign ♪</i>

05:08.391 --> 05:11.394
JOAN/TOM/CELESTE: ♪ 'Cause that's a sign ♪

05:11.561 --> 05:12.729
What you've written...

05:12.854 --> 05:16.065
it made me want to get
out of bed this morning.

05:16.065 --> 05:18.484
And that's quite rare.

05:18.484 --> 05:22.739
- Oh, I-I'm so relieved that you liked it.
- Liked it?

05:22.739 --> 05:24.365
The scene in the office,

05:24.365 --> 05:26.284
when Linda manipulates Mitchell's genitals

05:26.284 --> 05:27.910
until he begins to weep?

05:27.910 --> 05:29.704
It's a tour de force.

05:29.704 --> 05:31.539
Wow, thank you so much.

05:31.539 --> 05:34.417
And then to leave us
with this delicious mystery.

05:34.417 --> 05:37.211
The central question of the piece:

05:37.211 --> 05:38.713
why did Mitchell cry?

05:41.382 --> 05:45.136
Well, you'll just have
to read chapter two to find out.

05:45.386 --> 05:48.806
I called Gil Frond
first thing this morning.

05:48.806 --> 05:51.017
He teaches Intermediate to Advanced.

05:51.309 --> 05:54.395
He agreed to consider you for a slot.

05:54.395 --> 05:55.980
Oh, my goodness.

05:55.980 --> 05:57.440
He needs a writing sample

05:57.565 --> 05:59.817
at the end of tomorrow by the very latest.

05:59.817 --> 06:02.403
Oh, well, I can just give him the chapter.

06:02.403 --> 06:05.323
Gil has a 30-page sample requirement.

06:05.323 --> 06:07.742
If you could submit
the first two chapters?

06:07.742 --> 06:12.038
Well, I, I haven't
written chapter two yet.

06:12.038 --> 06:14.123
Oh, not on paper,

06:14.123 --> 06:16.626
but I'm sure you've
got it all figured out.

06:16.626 --> 06:19.337
What sort of a writer
would you be otherwise?

06:19.796 --> 06:20.922
Right.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.802
- Jiminator!
Hey.

06:25.802 --> 06:27.804
I was actually hopin' to maybe
grab a few minutes with you.

06:27.804 --> 06:29.555
Well, I was actually hopin'
to grab a few minutes with you.

06:29.972 --> 06:31.224
I've been doin' a lotta thinkin' about

06:31.224 --> 06:32.225
- bringin' in my own business--
Uh-huh.

06:32.225 --> 06:33.518
and I put together some ideas.

06:33.518 --> 06:35.478
Well, I just took
a gander at the invite list

06:35.478 --> 06:39.440
to Chad's bachelor party,
and you are on it, man.

06:39.982 --> 06:42.777
Wow. That's... flattering.

06:42.777 --> 06:45.196
Your trainer leaving her husband
for you is "flattering."

06:45.530 --> 06:49.867
An invite to Chad's
bachelor party is monumental.

06:49.867 --> 06:53.454
His dad is the CFO of a bank.

06:54.163 --> 06:57.375
One week in Aspen. We leave
next Monday. B.Y.O. skis.

06:57.583 --> 07:00.002
Guess I... better get some skis, then.

07:00.002 --> 07:02.380
Yeah, but here's the real
head-butt in the dick:

07:02.588 --> 07:03.881
you know that company in Texas,

07:03.881 --> 07:06.134
the one that makes cattle feed
from chicken shit?

07:06.134 --> 07:08.010
- Yeah.
- Q2 numbers just came in.

07:08.010 --> 07:09.053
Not looking good.

07:09.053 --> 07:11.055
Which means we're gonna
have to run all new projections

07:11.055 --> 07:12.682
before we head out to private equity.

07:12.682 --> 07:14.892
Which means I'm gonna need ya here,

07:14.892 --> 07:15.893
building out a new deck.

07:15.893 --> 07:17.103
Oh, okay--

07:17.103 --> 07:18.604
Right, but there's no way

07:18.604 --> 07:20.189
you're missing this party.

07:20.189 --> 07:22.108
Our chalet is a who's who of

07:22.108 --> 07:24.235
who decides who makes associate.
You have to be there.

07:24.944 --> 07:27.613
But I'm also supposed to be here?

07:27.989 --> 07:29.323
I know.

07:29.323 --> 07:30.700
I get it.

07:30.825 --> 07:32.702
This is one of those unsolvable
problems that you give

07:32.702 --> 07:34.495
to analysts to see if
they crack under the pressure.

07:34.495 --> 07:41.002
"Be there, but don't be there,
but also... be there."

07:41.794 --> 07:44.130
You have until Wednesday
to come up with a solve,

07:44.297 --> 07:48.718
at which point
your invite reverts to Chris.

07:50.803 --> 07:53.222
Oh hey, Germin, go fuck yourself.

08:08.154 --> 08:12.575
Miguel?! Miguel Jimenez?! Is that you?

08:12.909 --> 08:15.703
- Oh, goddammit.
- She knows exactly who you are.

08:15.703 --> 08:17.413
No one could forget that face.

08:17.413 --> 08:19.165
Drop to the floor.
Pretend you're having a seizure.

08:19.165 --> 08:22.043
It's Lindsay! Lindsay Arthur!

08:22.043 --> 08:24.795
This is not nice, what you're
doing. Not nice at all.

08:24.795 --> 08:26.714
Talk about crazy.

08:26.714 --> 08:29.133
No one said anything about crazy.

08:29.300 --> 08:33.429
What brings you to, uh,
this... neck of the woods?

08:33.429 --> 08:36.349
I work here. In the building
we're standing in front of.

08:36.349 --> 08:38.726
Tell her your base salary.
That'll really fuck her up.

08:38.726 --> 08:41.437
That's right. I completely forgot.

08:41.437 --> 08:44.524
If she forgot, she's an idiot.
If she's lying, she's a liar.

08:44.899 --> 08:46.400
Running into you like this?
Out of the blue?

08:46.400 --> 08:49.403
I mean... this is a sign.

08:49.403 --> 08:52.740
- Conjuring a fake sign?!
- A sign that...

08:52.740 --> 08:55.368
we both live in New York
and use the sidewalk?

08:55.368 --> 08:57.995
There he is. That's my boy.

08:57.995 --> 09:00.122
Hilarious. No.

09:00.122 --> 09:05.836
It is a sign that I should
finally ask you this question.

09:05.836 --> 09:08.089
I was wondering...

09:08.089 --> 09:09.549
Why did you cry when I fumbled

09:09.549 --> 09:11.759
with your private parts
like a clumsy juggler?

09:14.220 --> 09:16.722
...if you could ever forgive me

09:16.722 --> 09:18.307
for standing you up at the diner?

09:18.516 --> 09:21.894
Not in a million years.

09:21.894 --> 09:23.187
Already have.

09:24.522 --> 09:25.898
It's just-- I, I should've told you

09:25.898 --> 09:28.609
I... I came to New York to focus on myself

09:28.609 --> 09:30.236
and then find my voice as a writer.

09:30.236 --> 09:32.405
- But seriously... seriously,

09:32.405 --> 09:34.073
don't sweat it. I certainly didn't.

09:34.073 --> 09:35.283
Yeah, he only waited at the diner

09:35.283 --> 09:37.660
- for you for an hour and a half.
- Ooh, ooh! Uh.

09:37.660 --> 09:39.870
Get her to guess your
FICO score. That'll be a hoot.

09:39.870 --> 09:43.040
And now she has a stain on
her trousers. How charming.

09:43.040 --> 09:44.417
- Just shut up.
- Fuck off.

09:44.417 --> 09:45.334
Oh.

09:45.960 --> 09:48.045
Well, excuse me
for offering outstanding advice.

09:48.045 --> 09:50.548
You know, I-I-- Still, I would
like to make it up to you.

09:50.548 --> 09:51.841
How 'bout we grab that breakfast now?

09:51.841 --> 09:53.342
- My treat.
- It's 5:00.

09:53.342 --> 09:56.554
Hm, true. European lunch?
Old folks dinner?

09:56.554 --> 09:58.264
Look, I'm dealing with
a pretty big crisis at work

09:58.264 --> 09:59.932
and I need to dive back in
first thing tomorrow,

09:59.932 --> 10:01.726
- so if you could--
- Oh, my god! Way to bury the lede.

10:01.726 --> 10:04.103
I excel in a crisis. How 'bout this?

10:04.103 --> 10:05.229
We can grab a light snack,

10:05.229 --> 10:06.564
I will solve your work problem for you,

10:06.564 --> 10:08.941
and, uh, then we'll, uh, call it a day?

10:13.613 --> 10:15.364
What about... a bus?

10:15.364 --> 10:16.866
Have you considered a bus? It could work.

10:16.866 --> 10:20.036
It's... 30 hours each way.

10:20.036 --> 10:23.247
Okay, I can see how
that could be... difficult.

10:23.247 --> 10:25.583
So far, this has been very helpful.

10:25.583 --> 10:26.584
Here's a thought.

10:26.584 --> 10:28.461
Have you considered that maybe

10:28.461 --> 10:29.754
your bosses are using this

10:29.754 --> 10:31.922
as a made-up assignment to mess with you?

10:33.507 --> 10:35.509
Welcome to investment banking.

10:36.218 --> 10:38.929
Are there good things about your job?

10:43.392 --> 10:45.061
Well, the money doesn't hurt.

10:45.519 --> 10:47.980
Sounds a little superficial.

10:50.149 --> 10:52.276
It's not just the money.
I like the challenge.

10:52.276 --> 10:53.694
Hm.

10:53.694 --> 10:55.112
Ya don't eat, ya don't kill.

10:55.488 --> 10:57.073
It's the other way around.

10:58.115 --> 11:01.327
You know... you don't seem, like,

11:01.327 --> 11:04.872
incredibly... killer-ish to me.

11:06.207 --> 11:07.667
And how would you know what I'm like?

11:07.917 --> 11:12.755
Well, you know, you did... cry when--

11:13.047 --> 11:15.299
- Okay, yeah, no. I'm gonna go.
- Wait, wait. Miguel, wait.

11:15.299 --> 11:16.676
- Why did you cry?
- I don't know.

11:16.676 --> 11:17.843
Okay, perhaps,

11:17.843 --> 11:19.178
we could figure it out together.

11:19.178 --> 11:20.805
You know, have, like,
a brainstorming session.

11:20.805 --> 11:22.682
- I mean, if that would be helpful for you.
- Okay. Thank you

11:22.682 --> 11:24.308
- for the street nuts.
- Wait. Miguel!

11:24.308 --> 11:25.267
I have to go!

11:25.267 --> 11:26.977
Wait, no! But wait!

11:28.813 --> 11:31.148
Miguel, wait! You, you forgot your bag!

11:38.489 --> 11:42.493
- What?!
- I saw a bee on it and I panicked!

11:43.035 --> 11:44.453
How am I supposed to get it back?!

11:44.453 --> 11:47.331
Well, here, here, here, here.
Throw, throw mine.

11:47.331 --> 11:48.541
It's the least I can do.

11:48.833 --> 11:51.711
No, the least you can do
is to not throw my bag over!

11:52.128 --> 11:55.005
Well, the past is the past.
This is the least I can do now.

11:56.507 --> 11:57.383
I don't--

11:58.884 --> 12:00.428
You know, I used to be just like you.

12:00.428 --> 12:02.346
I was so afraid of breaking the rules.

12:02.346 --> 12:04.056
See, my dad is a coroner,

12:04.056 --> 12:05.391
and I spent my entire

12:05.391 --> 12:06.976
childhood hearing about
all the different ways

12:06.976 --> 12:09.228
I was gonna die or be permanently maimed.

12:09.478 --> 12:11.147
And then one day, I just realized,

12:11.147 --> 12:13.149
you cannot live like that.

12:13.524 --> 12:16.569
So, don't overthink it.
Don't even regular think it.

12:16.569 --> 12:17.653
Just.

12:24.118 --> 12:25.327
That was

12:26.495 --> 12:28.706
- oddly satisfying.
-  Right?

12:31.959 --> 12:34.962
I can't believe you did that.
My entire life is in that bag.

12:36.964 --> 12:38.591
What do we do now?

12:40.551 --> 12:42.052
Gimme a boost.

12:43.304 --> 12:44.972
Okay, well, what does,
what does that mean?

12:44.972 --> 12:47.266
- You push me up.
- Like, by the butt?

12:48.267 --> 12:50.394
You didn't do a lot of outdoor
playing as a child, did you?

12:50.394 --> 12:52.980
- Okay, I don't need the insults.
- Ready?

12:52.980 --> 12:54.607
- Yeah.
- One, two, three.

12:54.607 --> 12:56.984
Ooh, it's harder to get up--

12:56.984 --> 12:58.486
- Right there.
- You gotta--

12:58.486 --> 13:00.696
- If I can get the first leg up--
Yeah.

13:00.696 --> 13:02.782
then I can just--
Okay.

13:02.782 --> 13:04.867
- Yeah.
- If I can get this one--

13:07.578 --> 13:09.163
Maybe we should use the gate.

13:09.163 --> 13:12.041
Yeah, that works, too. All right.
- Okay. I'm comin' down.

13:15.961 --> 13:17.463
What is this thing?

13:18.339 --> 13:21.509
There used to be boulders
like this all over the city.

13:21.509 --> 13:23.427
From the last ice age.

13:24.470 --> 13:28.516
Most of 'em are gone, um,
bulldozed to put up high rises.

13:28.516 --> 13:29.600
But,

13:30.684 --> 13:31.727
I don't know.

13:32.645 --> 13:34.522
I always liked this one.

13:35.648 --> 13:37.066
No idea why.

13:37.650 --> 13:39.652
Because it is

13:40.361 --> 13:44.490
- truly... truly hideous.

13:50.204 --> 13:51.330
Hey.

13:52.748 --> 13:54.375
I really am sorry.

13:55.000 --> 13:58.379
About the diner...
And also, about earlier.

13:58.379 --> 14:00.506
It's... it's none of my business

14:00.506 --> 14:05.845
why you cried during...
hand stuff three weeks ago.

14:07.179 --> 14:09.223
I think I maybe do know why.

14:09.598 --> 14:11.267
Well, you don't,
you don't have to tell me.

14:11.642 --> 14:14.228
- Seriously.
- I guess I've just lost so much

14:14.228 --> 14:15.437
in my life.

14:16.981 --> 14:19.149
Things and people.

14:20.109 --> 14:22.528
And whenever life seems good, that's,

14:24.071 --> 14:26.198
that's always right before it goes bad.

